1 <!--66-->Goblin Archer<br />
2 <!--80-->Goblin Warrior<br />
1 Trolls Keyward<br />
2 Cave Troll of Moria<br />
1 Balrog, Flame of Udun<br />
2 Ulaire Nelya<br />
1 Ulaire Enquea    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">To start off, Bid 0-2. Ideally, you want to go second just to ensure that you are able to play your sight 3. Hopefully your opponet will be playing the pony, as you only play with one Aragorn, but if he doesnt its okay, Boromir is the most important companion once he has his horn. Whatever you do make sure you can play Rivendell Valley, because every time you play an elf with Silinde out, you get to draw a card. That is why I have 2 copies of Ulaire Nelya in the deck. Once you have Beren and Luthien and Mallorn Trees, you can use mallorn trees to put all of your extra copies on the bottom and you can exert  and ally to make a minion strenth minus one. It helps keep your elves alive when they dont have weapons, and it helps them kill minions when they are fully equipped. Use Boromir and his horn to bring up Elrond or Uruviel if your site 6 is out. If you exert twice for one of them they are strength 14, with Beren and Luthien to back them up.<br />
<br />
The shadow side uses moria archery to pile up the wounds on the opponets fellowship. The moria archer troops and marksman usually win skirmishes with a scimitar, so they stack on swarms and you keep playing a lot of archers.  The Goblin warrior, one of the most underrated and underused cards in the game, helps by getting rid of Thrarin, so a companion has to face the troll or rog, or gets rid of pesky dwarven conditions like Song of Durin.  Enquea is really nasty if your opponet has 7 companions out with a lot of archery they soaked up. He can potentially kill 2 companions with only 2 exertions. Massive archery totals have been showing up lately with gondor bowmen and Son of Thranduil, so the Goblin Archer really puts a thorn in the side of decks like that by making the fellowship archery total minus 6.  Your archers usually can slow the fellowship down the last couple of sites, so you can usually keep up or move ahead of them when you need to.<br />
<br />
This deck is fun to play. I love it when Elrond beats the Witch King with a Pale Blade, or the cave Troll goes down to Arwen.  Beren and Luthien makes this possible. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
